        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "25d396fad4fa4251",
        "text": "The GPL is a copyleft license, which means that derived works can only be distributed under the same license terms. This is in distinction to permissive free software licenses, of which the [[BSD license]]s and the [[MIT License]] are the standard examples. [[GPL]] was the first copyleft license for general use."
