      "text": "Code licensed under several other licenses can be combined with a program under the GPL without conflict, as long as the combination of restrictions on the work as a whole does not put any additional restrictions beyond what GPL allows.[https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html The GNU General Public License v3.0 – GNU Project – Free Software Foundation (FSF)] In addition to the regular terms of the GPL, there are additional restrictions and permissions one can apply:"
